  <h1>Hiware Bazar: A Success Story in Water Conservation and Community Development</h1>

  <img src="hiware_bazar_map.jpg" alt="Map of Hiware Bazar">

  <p>Hiware Bazar, located in Maharashtra, India, has transformed from a drought-stricken village to a model of sustainable development.  The key to its success has been a focus on water conservation and community participation.</p>

  <h2>Key Initiatives:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><b>Water Conservation:</b> Implemented various measures to recharge groundwater and manage water resources effectively.</li>
    <li><b>Community Involvement:</b>  The "four bandis" (bans on tree felling, free grazing, family planning, and liquor) were enacted with the support of the villagers.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Learn more about Hiware Bazar's journey from a struggling village to a thriving community on our website.</p>

  <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hiware_Bazar">Read more on Wikipedia</a>

